*prelude-lml-3.0.0 (05 Aug 2016)

  05 Aug 2016; Göktürk Yüksek <gokturk@gentoo.org>
  +files/prelude-lml-3.0.0-conf.patch,
  +files/prelude-lml-3.0.0-configure.patch,
  +files/prelude-lml-3.0.0-run.patch, +files/prelude-lml.initd,
  +files/prelude-lml.run, +files/prelude-lml.service, +metadata.xml,
  +prelude-lml-3.0.0.ebuild:
  New package

  Prelude-LML is a log analyser that allows Prelude to collect and
  analyze information from all kind of applications emitting logs or
  syslog messages in order to detect suspicious activities and transform
  them into Prelude-IDMEF alerts.

  24 Aug 2016; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> files/prelude-lml.initd:
  use #!/sbin/openrc-run instead of #!/sbin/runscript

  Package-Manager: portage-2.3.0

